                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1195</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-10T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1917—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 7 (8?), 10 p.m. You are instructed to ask for an interview with
                    President Menocal and to say that the situation in Cuba has been carefully
                    considered by the President of the United States and the Secretary of State and
                    that it is suggested that peaceful conditions may be sooner restored and further
                    destruction of valuable property be prevented, if he should ask for an
                    investigation and adjustment of the election question by General Crowder and
                    other representative Americans, as was intimated by him to you; that this
                    Government would be willing to lend its good offices to the Cuban people in this
                    respect.</p>
                <p>It is suggested that a proclamation, embodying this request should follow the
                    proclamation of President Menocal which was contained in your cable of March 8,
                    10 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
